   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Loima Pastoralists&#x2019; Capacity Strengthening Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is designed to strengthen the capacity of targeted livestock keepers to better plan and execute drought coping strategies in a manner that restores, protects and diversifies their livelihoods options therefore increasing their resilience against future droughts.

Outcome: Targeted livestock-dependent stakeholders protect their livelihood assets, particularly the strategic breeding stock. 

Output 1.1- Targeted households have access to emergency supplementary livestock feeds. 

Output 1.2- Targeted households have improved access to water for livestock and domestic use.</narrative>
  </description>
